Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into 1⁄2-inch-thick pieces. Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{a drizzle}, @salt{a pinch}, and @pepper{a pinch}. Roast on top rack until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Once roasted, carefully toss with @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon}.

While carrots roast, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{a drizzle} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add ginger and scallion whites; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 3⁄4 cup water (1 1⁄4 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, pat @pork chops{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; place between two large pieces of #plastic wrap{}. Pound with a #mallet{} or #rolling pin{} until pork is about 1⁄2 inch thick.

Place @panko breadcrumbs{1%cup}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, @salt{1%tsp}(for coating) and @pepper{to taste} in a #gallon-size zip-close bag{}.

Place @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon} in a #medium bowl{}; add pork and turn to evenly coat.

Add coated pork to bag with seasoned panko and seal to close. Shake until pork is evenly coated.

> TIP: You may need to move around pork chops in bag, pressing with your hands, to spread out panko and make it stick.

Heat a 1⁄4-inch layer of @cooking oil{a 1/4-inch layer} in a large, preferably #nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Once oil is shimmering and hot enough that a pinch of panko sizzles when added to pan, add coated pork (discard any remaining panko in bag).

Cook until panko is golden brown and pork is cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. (For 4 servings, cook in batches.)

Transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}.

Place @Bachan's Original Japanese Barbecue Sauce{1.75%ounce} in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave until warmed through, ~{30%seconds}.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tbsp}(for rice) and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Divide rice, pork, and carrots between plates. Drizzle pork with Bachan's Original Japanese Barbecue Sauce. Sprinkle with scallion greens and serve.

> Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145º.